  "text": "The xDS (Extensible Discovery Service) protocol is a set of APIs defined in envoyproxy/data-plane-api that allows dynamic configuration of Envoy proxies. The service definitions are organized in the envoy/service directory with both v2 (legacy) and v3 (active) versions.\n\nKey xDS services in envoy/service/*/v3/*.proto files include:\n\n1. **Discovery Services** (core xDS protocol for resource discovery):\n   - RouteDiscoveryService (envoy/service/route/v3/rds.proto) with rpc StreamRoutes, DeltaRoutes, FetchRoutes\n   - ClusterDiscoveryService (envoy/service/cluster/v3/cds.proto) with rpc StreamClusters, DeltaClusters, FetchClusters\n   - EndpointDiscoveryService (envoy/service/endpoint/v3/eds.proto) with rpc StreamEndpoints, DeltaEndpoints, FetchEndpoints\n   - ListenerDiscoveryService (envoy/service/listener/v3/lds.proto) with rpc DeltaListeners, StreamListeners\n   - SecretDiscoveryService (envoy/service/secret/v3/sds.proto) with rpc StreamSecrets, DeltaSecrets, FetchSecrets\n   - ScopedRoutesDiscoveryService (envoy/service/route/v3/srds.proto) with rpc StreamScopedRoutes, DeltaScopedRoutes, FetchScopedRoutes\n   - RuntimeDiscoveryService (envoy/service/runtime/v3/rtds.proto) with rpc StreamRuntime, DeltaRuntime, FetchRuntime\n   - LocalityEndpointDiscoveryService (envoy/service/endpoint/v3/leds.proto)\n   - VirtualHostDiscoveryService (envoy/service/route/v3/rds.proto)\n\n2. **Aggregated Discovery Service** (multiplexes all resource types):\n   - AggregatedDiscoveryService (envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads.proto) with rpc StreamAggregatedResources\n\n3. **Administrative and Special Services**:\n   - HealthDiscoveryService (envoy/service/health/v3/hds.proto) with rpc StreamHealthCheck, FetchHealthCheck\n   - ClientStatusDiscoveryService (envoy/service/status/v3/csds.proto) with rpc StreamClientStatus, FetchClientStatus\n   - TapSinkService (envoy/service/tap/v3/tap.proto) with rpc StreamTaps\n\n4. **External Service Integrations**:\n   - Authorization (envoy/service/auth/v3/external_auth.proto) with rpc Check\n   - ExternalProcessor (envoy/service/ext_proc/v3/external_processor.proto) with rpc Process\n   - RedisProxyExternalAuth (envoy/service/redis_auth/v3/redis_external_auth.proto) with rpc Authenticate\n\nThe v2 versions provide backward compatibility and are found in envoy/service/discovery/v2/ and envoy/service/auth/v2/.\n\nThe grpc/grpc repository implements the standard gRPC Health Checking Protocol defined in src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto, which defines the Health service with rpc Check and Watch methods. Implementations are provided in multiple languages:\n- C++: src/cpp/server/health/ (default_health_check_service.cc/h, health_check_service.cc)\n- Python: src/python/grpcio_health_checking/grpc_health/v1/ (health.py, _async.py)\n- Ruby: src/ruby/pb/grpc/health/checker.rb\n\nWhile the gRPC Health service and Envoy's xDS services serve different purposes (health checking vs. dynamic configuration), both are gRPC-based service definitions that represent critical infrastructure patterns used in modern microservice environments. The Health service is a standard component that complements xDS deployments by providing health status information to load balancers and service meshes."
